# Parallel-agent worktrees — the Agent tool's `isolation: "worktree"` mode
# creates a fresh git worktree under .claude/worktrees/agent-<id>/ for
# each isolated sub-agent. They're tooling artifacts (a separate git
# checkout), not project work, so they MUST be ignored — committing them
# would trigger infinite recursion and break the hook check.
.claude/worktrees/
